estival crowd, the other said to invoke the atmosphere of Last Night of the Proms.</p><p>We are curious to see how this will all end up. Will the ceremony be a witty and impressively epic paen to Britishness, or a mind-boggling post-modern mess?</p><p>This is where you come in. We're fascinated to see how this ends up looking, and we want to see your creative interpretations of the show. So we're setting up a special edition of The Gallery - here, as an example, is <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/gallery/2012/jun/05/euro-2012-predictions-the-gallery\">what our readers predicted for Euro 2012</a>. <strong>Email your photoshopped masterpieces to gallery@guardian.co.uk by midday on Wednesday 13 June</strong>, complete with a caption. We will share the best we receive in a gallery - and the top three will also win a prize.</p>","productionOffice":"UK","showInRelatedContent":"true","hasStoryPackage":"true","internalPageCode":"1758526","publication":"theguardian.com","trailText":"<p>Danny Boyle has revealed his surreal vision for the opening ceremony. Now we want you to send us your interpretations</p>","allowUgc":"false","lastModified":"2014-08-19T19:41:17Z","headline":"London 2012: tell us how the opening ceremony might look","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"391480937"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2012/jun/12/olympics-2012-ceremony-predictions-the-gallery","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/sport/2012/jun/12/olympics-2012-ceremony-predictions-the-gallery","sectionName":"Sport","elements":[{"id":"gu-image-391482634","relation":"main","type":"image","assets":[{"type":"image","mimeType":"image/jpeg","file":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2012/6/12/1339501161224/A-handout-picture-showing-008.jpg","typeData":{"displayCredit":"true","source":"PA","photographer":"Dave Poultney","altText":"A handout picture showing plans for the London 2012 Olympic Games Opening Cer