or the electronics brand.</p><p>Her new mount, which she has ridden sporadically throughout her career, is not considered to be in the same class as Toytown. But after finishing third at Bramham, she spoke of High Kingdom's rapid improvement and that, combined with her experience as a rider in major competitions, is likely to have tipped the balance in her favour.</p><p>Phillips, who is married to former England rugby captain Mike Tindall, said: \"It's awesome to be given this opportunity.</p><p>\"I am really excited and can't wait to kick on and get him there. Hopefully, we will make it this time.\"</p><p>Phillips's mother, Princess Anne, competed in the 1976 Olympic Games as a member of the British team in Montreal on the Queen's horse Goodwill. As a representative on the International Olympic Committee, she was a vocal advocate of the campaign to bring the Games to London. Phillips's father, Captain Mark Phillips, won a gold medal in 1972 and a silver in 1988.</p><p>A BOA spokesman said: \"I can't comment on who has been selected until the team has been officially announced later this week.\"</p><p>Phillips will take one of five slots on the eventing team in a sport expected to deliver medals for Team GB.</p><p>Part of the rationale for holding the equestrian events in central London in Greenwich Park as opposed to a venue further from the athletes' village is to appeal to spectators and TV viewers who have not considered watching it before.</p><p>The presence of the 13th in line to the throne in eventing competition is only likely to add to the interest and anticipation around an event that was among the first to sell out when tickets went on sale last year.</p><p>• This article was amended on 12 June 2012 to make clear that it was Zara Phillips's father, not Princess Anne's, who won Olympic medals in 1972 and 1988.</p>","internalOctopusCode":"6288621","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2012-06-12T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"true","internalPageCod